emsl:project_160707 a lambdaber:Study ;
    dcterms:title "Understanding the multi-drug resistance mechanisms in fungal pathogen" ;
    lambdaber:description "Fungal diseases claim over 1.5 million lives annually and affect more than a billion people worldwide, presenting a significant challenge due to increasing drug resistance. A primary mechanism underlying this resistance is drug efflux, mediated by the overexpression of ATP-binding cassette and major facilitator superfamily transporters. In this proposal, we aim to determine the structures of drug transporters in Candida species, human fungal pathogens, to gain molecular insights into substrate recognition and the various steps of the transport cycle. We have successfully expressed and purified the transporters of interest. Following optimization, we obtained high-resolution cryo-EM structures in the apo state for two of these transporters. Through this proposal, we seek support to collect cryo-EM data to resolve the structures of these transporters in complex with various substrates and antifungal drugs, and in different functional states throughout the transport cycle." ;
    lambdaber:keywords "EMSL",
        "General Access" .

